==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-spoils.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔɪlz|-ɔɪlz]]

===Noun===
'''spoils''' (plural only; not used in singular form)
#That which is taken from another by [[violence]]; especially, the [[plunder]] taken from an [[enemy]]; pillage; booty.
#:''"Gentle gales, Fanning their odoriferous wings, dispense Native perfumes, and whisper whence they stole Those balmy spoils."'' &mdash;Milton.
#Public [[offices]] and their benefits regarded as the peculiar property of a successful party or faction, to be bestowed for its own advantage; -- commonly in the plural; as 
#:''to the victor belong the spoils''

===Verb===
'''spoils'''
# Third person singular simple present form of ''to [[spoil]].''
#:''Milk '''spoils''' when left out too long.''

